@startuml Kamelot Author - Usage Sequence Diagram

skinparam backgroundColor #FAFAFA
skinparam sequenceArrowThickness 2
skinparam sequenceArrowColor #F59E0B
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBorderColor #334155
skinparam sequenceLifeLineBackgroundColor #F8FAFC
skinparam participant {
  BackgroundColor #FFFFFF
  BorderColor #334155
  FontColor #1E293B
}
skinparam actor {
  BorderColor #334155
  FontColor #1E293B
}
skinparam note {
  BackgroundColor #FEF3C7
  BorderColor #F59E0B
  FontColor #1E293B
}
skinparam divider {
  BackgroundColor #E2E8F0
  BorderColor #94A3B8
  FontColor #475569
}

title Kamelot Author — Usage Sequence Diagram

actor "User\n(RE / Analyst / Dev)" as User
participant "Browser\n(Next.js UI)" as UI
participant "/api/generate" as GenAPI
participant "AnthropicProvider\n(ILLMProvider)" as LLM
participant "Claude Sonnet API" as Claude
participant "camel-parser.ts" as Parser
participant "KrokiRenderer\n(IDiagramRenderer)" as Kroki
participant "kroki.io" as KrokiSvc
participant "/api/validate" as ValAPI
participant "/api/execute" as ExecAPI
participant "JBangExecutor\n(IRouteExecutor)" as JBangEx
participant "Camel JBang\n(persistent)" as JBang
participant "AviationStack API" as Aviation

== Startup ==

JBang -> JBang : pre-warm process\n(on server start)
note right : First execution is fast\nbecause JBang is already running

== Step 1: User Describes Integration ==

User -> UI : types integration prompt\n"Get all international flights arriving\nat Dubai International Airport..."
UI -> UI : enable Generate button

alt Optional: PlantUML upload
  User -> UI : uploads .puml file
  UI -> UI : show "PlantUML uploaded" badge
end

== Step 2: Generate Route ==

User -> UI : clicks [Generate]
UI -> UI : disable Generate button\nshow loading spinner
UI -> GenAPI : POST /api/generate\n{ prompt | plantuml }

GenAPI -> LLM : generateRoute(prompt)
LLM -> Claude : Anthropic SDK call\n(system prompt + user prompt)

note over Claude
  Generates in one response:
  1. Apache Camel YAML DSL route
  2. PlantUML sequence diagram
  Returns strict JSON: { yaml, plantuml }
end note

Claude --> LLM : { yaml: "...", plantuml: "@startuml..." }
LLM --> GenAPI : { yaml, plantuml }

== Step 3: Validate Route (internal) ==

GenAPI -> ValAPI : POST /api/validate { yaml }
ValAPI --> GenAPI : { valid: true | errors: [...] }

== Step 4: Encode Diagram ==

GenAPI -> Kroki : renderDiagram(plantuml)
Kroki -> Kroki : base64-encode PlantUML
Kroki -> KrokiSvc : GET /plantuml/svg/<encoded>
KrokiSvc --> Kroki : SVG image
Kroki --> GenAPI : svgUrl

== Step 5: Parse YAML → Graph ==

GenAPI -> Parser : parseYaml(yaml)
Parser --> GenAPI : { nodes[], edges[] }

GenAPI --> UI : { yaml, plantuml, svgUrl, nodes, edges }

== Step 6: Populate UI ==

UI -> UI : fade-in result panels
UI -> UI : [YAML tab] render in Monaco editor\n(read-only, syntax highlighted)
UI -> UI : [Flow tab] render React Flow canvas\nfrom nodes + edges
UI -> UI : [Sequence tab] render SVG\nfrom svgUrl (Kroki)
UI -> UI : enable Test Route button
UI -> UI : re-enable Generate button

note over UI
  Developer View: Flow diagram + YAML
  Analyst View: Sequence diagram
  User can switch tabs freely
end note

User -> UI : reviews generated route\n(Flow / YAML / Sequence tabs)

== Step 7: Test the Route ==

User -> UI : clicks [Test Route]
UI -> UI : disable Test button\nshow "Executing..." in TestPanel
UI -> ExecAPI : POST /api/execute { yaml }

ExecAPI -> JBangEx : execute(yaml)
JBangEx -> JBangEx : write YAML to /tmp/kamelot/<id>.yaml\ninject AVIATIONSTACK_API_KEY as JVM property
JBangEx -> JBang : run <file>.yaml --max-seconds=15\n-Daviationstack.api.key=***

JBang -> Aviation : GET /v1/flights\n?access_key=***&arr_iata=DXB&flight_status=active
Aviation --> JBang : JSON payload\n(flight records)

JBang -> JBang : unmarshal JSON\nlog result

JBang --> JBangEx : stdout + stderr
JBangEx --> ExecAPI : { output, exitCode }

alt JBang not installed
  JBangEx --> ExecAPI : { error: "JBang not installed" }
  ExecAPI --> UI : 503 { message: "JBang not installed.\nPlease install JBang to run routes." }
  UI -> UI : show error in TestPanel
else Timeout (>20s)
  JBangEx --> ExecAPI : { output: partial, timeout: true }
  ExecAPI --> UI : 200 { output: partial, timeout: true }
  UI -> UI : show partial output + timeout warning
else Success
  ExecAPI --> UI : 200 { output, exitCode: 0 }
  UI -> UI : stream real flight data\ninto TestPanel\n(flight number, airline,\norigin city, arrival time)
end

User -> UI : reads real flight results

@enduml
